<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Sorry to hear about your own loss. I'm glad you felt so strongly about Gwen and Royce to feel the way you do. I can assure you I don't take death ligh<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Sorry to hear about your own loss. I'm glad you felt so strongly about Gwen and Royce to feel the way you do. I can assure you I don't take death lightly and there were reasons for things to happen the way you do. Since you only have Percepliquis to go, I do suggest you keep reading. The book is all about redemption and I think you'll like the way it turns out.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
