  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2671959793" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2671959793" />
    <a title="Deborah Obida" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida"><img alt="Deborah Obida" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604679377p2/54790180.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2671959793?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah Obida" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah Obida" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida">Deborah Obida</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780748131372" href="/book/show/20451875-heir-of-novron">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=favorite-books">favorite-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2671959793" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11013333218479726247"><b>
  <i>‘More valuable than gold, more precious than life, is mercy bestowed upon he who hast not known its soft kiss’—Girard Hily, Proverbs of the Soul.</i>
</b><br/><br/>Nothing is as good as when the final book in a series is also the best in the series. The author did an amazing job in this book. All the strings are tied, I can&apos;t think of anything that the author didn&apos;t end well, that is how good this book is.<br/><br/><b>
  <i>“What is the advantage of fear, or the benefit of regret, or the bonus of granting misery a foothold ev</i></b></span>
  <span id="freeText11013333218479726247" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>‘More valuable than gold, more precious than life, is mercy bestowed upon he who hast not known its soft kiss’—Girard Hily, Proverbs of the Soul.</i>
</b><br /><br />Nothing is as good as when the final book in a series is also the best in the series. The author did an amazing job in this book. All the strings are tied, I can't think of anything that the author didn't end well, that is how good this book is.<br /><br /><b>
  <i>“What is the advantage of fear, or the benefit of regret, or the bonus of granting misery a foothold even if death is embracing you? My old abbot used to say, ‘Life is only precious if you wish it to be.’ I look at it like the last bite of a wonderful meal—do you enjoy it, or does the knowledge that there is no more to follow make it so bitter that you would ruin the experience?”</i>
</b><br /><br />Like any great fantasy book, we lost some lovable characters. The fight scenes were portrayed very well.<br /><br /><br />I adore the world building and writing so much, just like the previous books this book is set in a whole new different location and a few of the old ones. The book os written in third person multiple POV.<br /><br /><b>
  <i>“It doesn’t take much to please you, does it, Myron?”<br />“Antun Bulard once wrote ‘When you expect nothing from the world—not the light of the sun, the wet of water, nor the air to breathe—everything is a wonder and every moment a gift.’ ”<br />“And you expect nothing from the world?”<br />He looked at her, puzzled. “I’m a monk.”</i>
</b><br /><br />I finally got to know who the heir is and it was mind blowing,<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Royce is the heir and my ship finally sailed, Arista and Hadrian <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> I have to admit I so did not see that coming, the revelation was glorious. Lots of things happened in this book and they are all amazingly glorious.<br /><br />There are lots of new characters in this book but Breckton, Allie and Mercy are my favourites amongst the new characters. Breckton is Wesley's elder brother, he is what a knight should be. Allie and Mercy are just two small girls that everyone loves.<br /><br />Royce, Hadrian, Arista, Amilia and Modina are amazing as ever.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11013333218479726247" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

